<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-200-818  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 200 818.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  April 19 1989 n1159* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>British Telecom to try multi-media fibre services in 1990.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Telecommunications PLC (services).andO;Topic:     Multimode FibersFiber OpticsTelecommunicationsTelephone SystemsStrategic Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BRITISH TELECOM TO TRY MULTI-MEDIA FIBRE SERVICES IN 1990andM;British Telecommunications Plc plans next year a public trial of multi-mediafibre optic systems with about 500 business and residential customers inBishops Stortford, Hertfordshire.andP;  The #5m experiment will involve opticalfibre links transmitting stereo television, high fidelity stereo radio andother services as well as telephone calls.andP;  The trial will enable BritishTelecom to assess two types of fibre system, Telephony Over Passive Networksand Broadband Integrated Distributed Star.andP;  The former uses a series of inertfibre splitters, or couplers, to direct services to each customer, initiallyonly telephone speech and low-speed data, but ultimately television, hi-firadio and access to a video library.andP;  Broadband Integrated Distributed Star,a more ad-vanced system, uses electronic switches to route specific servicesthat have been requested by individual users.andO;</TEXT></DOC>